13) Q: Difference between Subject and BehaviorSubject?

Answer:

Subject does not store previous values.

If subscriber joins late, it misses old data.

BehaviorSubject stores the latest value and immediately sends it to new subscribers.

We mostly used BehaviorSubject for shared data like logged-in user info and application state.


